    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Just noting this for future reference; I don't think we want to get distracted by another policy change any time soon. \r\n\r\nRecently I learned about [DCO](https://blog.docker.com/2014/01/docker-code-contributions-require-developer-certificate-of-origin/), a more \"passive\" approach to managing contribution red tape, avoiding the need for a CLA. \r\n\r\nDisadvantages:\r\n- it requires some setup on the contributor's end\r\n  - @elmart's tooling for \"commit trailers\" could help with this maybe\r\n- we may need to rewrite past commit messages (not certain about this)\r\n\r\nother reference: https://blog.chef.io/2016/09/19/introducing-developer-certificate-of-origin/",
